# ğŸ bug report

### Description

Angular service worker ignores images that are specified in dataGroups when using the performance strategy.

## ğŸ”¬ Minimal Reproduction

1. First make the browser/service worker cache is cleared
2. Here is an example section from ngsw-config.json
```
{
	"name": "photos",
	"urls": [
		"/api/photo/**"
	],
	"cacheConfig": {
		"strategy": "performance",
		"maxSize": 1000,
		"maxAge": "7d"
	}
}
```
3. Browse to a page which has an html img tag to an image with the path that is covered by the url specified (see above step)

4. Look at the network requests and you will see that a network request is made everytime, the service worker is not caching the image

**NOTE** When using the freshness strategy images are cached and works correctly.

